  "texts": [
    "The parameter optimizer we used for the model is Adam, and the initial learning rate was fixed at 0.001.",
    "In order to improve the quality of the model, data augmentation was performed during the training process.",
    "The trade-off parameters of the cross-entropy loss and the center loss were set to 1 and 0.008, respectively.",
    "The equations for cross-entropy loss, center loss, and total Loss are given by:L CE = - 1 N N i=1 M j=1 y i j log( ŷi j) (6)Where:• N is the number of training samples.• M is the number of classes.• y i j is a binary indicator (0 or 1) if class label j is the correct classification for input i.• ŷi j is the predicted probability of input i belonging to class j.L center = 1 2 N i=1 f (x i) -c y i 2 2(7)Where:• f (x i) is the feature representation of sample i.• c y i is the center of the feature representations of class y i.• • 2 denotes the Euclidean distance.L = L CE + λL center (8)Where λ is the trade-off parameter between the cross-entropy loss and the center loss.Our experiments were carried out on a GPU with the following configuration: Intel(R) Xeon(R) E5-2670 v3 CPU, 64GB memory, GeForce GTX TITAN X, and 12GB of display memory.",
    "In our experiment, we conducted training and testing of models using three different datasets: PatternNEt, Eurosat, and RSSCN7."
  ],
